Grounds for Divorce

In Seychelles, you can only obtain a divorce if you can prove that your marriage has irretrievably broken down. The court will consider the following grounds for divorce:

Adultery

Unreasonable behaviour

Desertion

Two years separation with consent

Five years separation without consent

The court will not consider the following grounds for divorce:

You have been separated for less than two years

You have been separated for less than five years

You have been married for less than one year

You have been married for less than three months and have not yet had a child

You have been married for less than three months and have had a child

You have been married for less than three months and have had a child and the child is less than 16 years old

You have been married for less than three months and have had a child and the child is less than 16 years old and you have been separated for less than two years

You have been married for less than three months and have had a child and the child is less than 16 years old and you have been separated for less than two years and you have not lived together for at least one year
